	<text>
		<body>
			<div type="transcription">
				<div type="original" xml:lang="cs">
					<pb facs="EHRI-ET-JMP006_01.jpg" n="1"/>
					<p rend="center">Úryvek z <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-716" type="subject">dopisu</term></p>
					<p>na pana <persName ref="#ehri_et_glaser_hugo">Hugo Glasera</persName>, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Praha</placeName> XII., <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Zelená</placeName> 7, od p. <persName
							ref="#ehri_et_burg_berthold">Bertholda Burga</persName>, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">vězně</term> z <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">koncentračních táborů</term>
							v <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-513">Lodži</placeName>, <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-1444" type="camp">Poznani</placeName>, <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2"
							>Auschwitz</placeName> a <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-15" type="camp">Fürstengrube</placeName>, t. č. tlumočníka <foreign xml:lang="eng">Interpreter with Co.C</foreign> 823 T.D.Bn. A.P.O. 339, <orgName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004289" type="subject"><foreign xml:lang="eng">U.S.Army</foreign></orgName>
						<foreign xml:lang="eng">c/o Postmaster N.Y.</foreign></p>
					<p>Milí <persName ref="#ehri_et_glaser_hugo">Glaserovi</persName>,</p>
					<p>právě jsem dostal <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-716" type="subject">dopis</term> od Napoleona a mám dětinskou radost, že jste zdrávi a že jste opět doma. Dověděl jsem se o Vás v <date when="1944-10">říjnu loňského roku</date>, že
						jste v <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-449" type="ghetto">Terezíně</placeName> a že se Vám daří dobře, <persName ref="#ehri_et_glaser_hugo">Hugaček</persName> že dělá v pekárně, a že se Vám narodil po 9 letech – místo po 9 měsících – <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824">kluk</term>. Kde pak je to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">dítě</term>?</p>
					<p>Moje matka šla do <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-499" type="subject">plynu</term>.</p>
					<p>Mám pro Vás jednu smutnou zprávu, ale viděli jste přece tolik, že není nám třeba okolků, i když jde o ty, kteří nám jsou nejbližší.</p>
					<p>Toto se přihodilo: <date when="1943-12-18">18. prosince 1943</date>, když jsme byli v <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">lágru</term>
						<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-15" type="camp">Fürstengrube</placeName> u <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2">Auschwitz</placeName>, kolem půlnoci, vrátila se odpolední směna do <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">tábora</term>. Já jsem tehdy byl v <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-491" type="subject">KB</term>. měl jsem po úrazu v dole těžký výron krve do kotníku a co ještě.
							<persName ref="#ehri_et_glaser_max">Max</persName> byl <foreign xml:lang="de">Vorarbeitrem</foreign> v odpolední šichtě.</p>
					<p>2 dny předtím přišli <distinct type="camp_language">Zugangy</distinct> do <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">lágru</term>, <placeName ref="#ehri_et_galicia">galiciáni</placeName> – <placeName ref="#ehri_et_galicia"
							>haličtí</placeName> Židé. Někteří měli domov velmi blízko, na hranicích Horního <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3066138/silesia.html">Slezska</placeName> a <placeName ref="#ehri_et_galicia">Haliče</placeName>. Jeden z nich <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">utekl</term> při nástupu u šachtu. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term> měla toho dne <foreign xml:lang="de">Julfest</foreign>. Šichta se
						vrátila do <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">lágru</term>, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-294" type="subject">Lagerführer</term>- <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-294" type="subject">Hauptscharführer</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_moll_otto">Moll</persName> - /pamatuji si to jméno, je to jeden z největších vrahů z celého <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2">Auschwitz</placeName>, <placeName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2">Birkenau</placeName> a okolí/ v podnapilém stavu dal nastoupit. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-634" type="subject">Vyslýchal</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-485" type="subject">Capo</term>, pak <foreign xml:lang="de">Vorarbeitera</foreign>-<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject"><foreign xml:lang="de"
						>Häftlinga</foreign></term>, kdo <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">utekl</term> a tím <foreign xml:lang="de">Vorarbeiterem</foreign> byl na neštěstí <persName ref="#ehri_et_glaser_max">Max</persName>. <persName
							ref="#ehri_et_glaser_max">Max</persName> myslel, že věc <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-294" type="subject"><foreign xml:lang="de">Lagerführerovi</foreign></term> vysvětlí a že ho uklidní, ale přepočítal se. <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-294" type="subject"><foreign xml:lang="de">Lagerführer</foreign></term> ho <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">zastřelil</term>, a pak ještě 5 nebo 6 <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject"><foreign xml:lang="de">Häftlingů</foreign></term>. byl by střílel dále, kdyby ho nebyl zastavil jeho zástupce, tehdejší, <persName ref="#ehri_et_schmidt_max">Max Schmidt</persName>, který později
						byl naším <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-294" type="subject"><foreign xml:lang="de">Lagerführerem</foreign></term>. </p>
					<p>V <date when="1944-12">prosinci 1944</date> jsem se stal <foreign xml:lang="de"><distinct type="camp_language">Rapportschreiberem</distinct></foreign> a našel jsem protokol následujícího obsahu:</p>
					<p>Dne <date when="1944-12-08">8. 12. 1944</date> vrátila se odpolední šichta o obvyklé hodině za leteckého poplachu do <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">lágru</term>. <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject"><foreign xml:lang="de">Häftling</foreign></term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_glaser_max">Max Glaser</persName>, <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_czechs" type="subject">český</term> Žid, náhle napadl jednoho <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS-mana</term>, využívaje úplného
							<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-624" type="subject">zatemnění</term> a snažil se mu vyrvati strojní pistoli. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SSák</term> se ho ale ubránil,
						použil zbraně a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">usmrtil</term> ho. Zmatku využili někteří <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject"><foreign xml:lang="de">Häftlingové</foreign></term>,
						aby se pokusili o hromadný <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">útěk</term>– <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject"><foreign xml:lang="de">Massenausbruch</foreign></term>. Strážní ihned po
						nich pálili, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">zastřelili</term> dalších 5 nebo 6, jeden <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">unikl</term>. Následovaly podpisy.</p>
					<p>Možná, že jste se o tom dověděli již dříve, toto jsou fakta, která mám od očitých svědků.</p>
					<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-657" type="subject">Dokumentační akce</term>:</p>
					<p>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_schmiedt_alexander">Alex. Schmiedt</persName>
						<date when="1945-09-12">12.9.1945</date>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_shek_zeev">Sheck</persName>
					</p>
				</div>
				<div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
					<pb facs="EHRI-ET-JMP006_01.jpg" n="1"/>
					<p>Passage from a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-716" type="subject">letter</term></p>
					<p>to Mr. <persName ref="#ehri_et_glaser_hugo">Hugo Glaser</persName>, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Prague</placeName> XII., <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Zelená 7</placeName>, from Mr. <persName
							ref="#ehri_et_burg_berthold">Berthold Burg</persName>, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">prisoner</term> of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">concentration camps</term>
							in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-513">Lodz</placeName>, <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-1444" type="camp">Poznan</placeName>, <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2"
							>Auschwitz</placeName> and <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-15" type="camp">Fürstengrube</placeName>, current profession interpreter with Co.C 823 T.D.Bn. A.P.O. 339, <orgName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004289" type="subject">U.S.Army</orgName> c/o Postmaster N.Y.</p>
					<p>Dear <persName ref="#ehri_et_glaser_hugo">Glasers</persName>,</p>
					<p>I have just received a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-716" type="subject">letter</term> from Napoleon and I am as happy as a child to hear that you are healthy and home once again. In <date when="1944-10">October</date> last year,
						I learned that you were in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-449" type="ghetto">Theresienstadt</placeName> and that you were doing well, that little <persName ref="#ehri_et_glaser_hugo">Hugo</persName> was working in a bakery, and that after
						9 years – instead of after 9 months – you had a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">boy</term>. Where, pray, is this <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">child</term>?</p>
					<p>My mother was <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-499" type="subject">gassed</term>.</p>
					<p>I have some sad news for you, but you have seen so much that we need not hesitate, especially when it concerns our dearest loved ones.</p>
					<p>This is what happened: on <date when="1943-12-18">December 18th, 1943</date>, when we were in the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-15" type="camp">Fürstengrube </placeName><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508"
							type="subject">camp</term> near <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2">Auschwitz</placeName>, around midnight, the afternoon shift returned to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term>.
						I was in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-491" type="subject">KB</term> at the time. After being injured in the mine, I had a bad hemorrhage in my ankle and whatnot. <persName ref="#ehri_et_glaser_max">Max</persName> was a <foreign xml:lang="de"
							>Vorarbeiter</foreign> on the afternoon shift.</p>
					<p>Two days earlier, <distinct type="camp_language">zugangi</distinct> arrived in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term> – <placeName ref="#ehri_et_galicia">Galicians</placeName> – Jews from <placeName
							ref="#ehri_et_galicia">Galicia</placeName>. Some lived nearby, on the border of Upper <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3066138/silesia.html">Silesia</placeName> and <placeName ref="#ehri_et_galicia">Galicia</placeName>. One of them <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escaped</term> at the start of his shift. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term> was celebrating <foreign xml:lang="de">Julfest</foreign>
						that day. When the shift returned to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term>, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-294" type="subject">Lagerführer</term>- <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-294" type="subject">Hauptscharführer</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_moll_otto">Moll</persName> (I remember his name, he’s one of the biggest murderers in all of <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2">Auschwitz</placeName>, <placeName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2">Birkenau</placeName> and their surroundings) was drunk when he let them in. He <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-634" type="subject">interrogated</term> the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-485" type="subject">capo</term> and then <foreign xml:lang="de">Vorarbeiter</foreign>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">Häftling</term> to find out who had <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escaped</term>, and, unfortunately, that <foreign xml:lang="de"
							>Vorarbeiter</foreign> was <persName ref="#ehri_et_glaser_max">Max</persName>. <persName ref="#ehri_et_glaser_max">Max</persName> thought that he could explain everything to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-294"
							type="subject">Lagerführer</term> and calm him down, but he miscalculated. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-294" type="subject">Lagerführer</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">shot</term> him and 5 or 6 other <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">Häftlings</term>. He would have shot more if <persName
							ref="#ehri_et_schmidt_max">Max Schmidt</persName>, his deputy at the time, hadn’t stopped him. Later, <persName ref="#ehri_et_schmidt_max">Max Schmidt</persName> became our <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-294" type="subject"
							>Lagerführer</term>.</p>
					<p>I became a <distinct type="camp_language">Rapportschreiber</distinct> in <date when="1944-12">December 1944</date>, and I discovered a statement with the following contents:</p>
					<p>On <date when="1944-12-08">8. 12. 1944</date> the afternoon shift returned to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term> at the usual hour during an air raid siren. <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">Häftling</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_glaser_max">Max Glaser</persName>, a <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_czechs" type="subject">Czech</term> Jew, suddenly attacked an <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS-man</term>, using the cover of a
						total <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-624" type="subject">blackout</term>, and tried to grab his service pistol. But the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS-man</term> managed to
						defend himself, discharged his weapon, and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">killed</term> him. Several <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">häftlings</term> used the confusion to
						attempt a mass <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escape</term> – <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject"><foreign xml:lang="de">Massenausbruch</foreign></term>. The guards immediately
						opened fire on them, and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">shot</term> another 5 or 6; one <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escaped</term>. This was followed by signatures.</p>
					<p>Maybe you have heard about this already. These are the facts I’ve received from eyewitnesses.</p>
					<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-657" type="subject">Documentation campaign</term>:</p>
					<p>
